  1. suv . suv cty( ) . .
mpg2<- mpg %>% 
  filter(class=='suv') %>% 
  group_by(manufacturer) %>% 
  summarise(avg_cty=mean(cty)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(avg_cty)) %>% 
  head(5) 
ggplot(mpg2, aes(x=reorder(manufacturer, -avg_cty), y=avg_cty)) +
  geom_bar(stat='identity',aes(fill=manufacturer)) +
  labs(title = "suv       Top5", x = "", y = "")

  1. class( ) compact, subcompact, suv cty( ) . cty .
m_c <- mpg %>% 
  filter(class %in% c("compact","subcompact","suv"))
m_c %>% 
  ggplot(aes(class, cty, col=class)) +
  geom_boxplot()+
  ggtitle("  cty") +labs(x=" ", y="")

  1. cut .
ggplot(diamonds, aes(cut, price, fill=cut)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + 
  scale_fill_brewer(palette='Spectral')+
  ggtitle("Cut   ") + xlab("Type of Cut") + ylab("Diamond Price") + coord_cartesian(ylim=c(0,7500))

  1. cut color .
m_p <- diamonds %>% 
  group_by(cut,color) %>% 
  summarise(m_p=mean(price))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'cut'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
ggplot(m_p, aes(cut, m_p)) + 
  geom_bar(stat='identity',aes(fill=cut)) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette='Set3') +
  ggtitle("color  cut  ") +
  labs(x="cut", y="price")+
  facet_wrap(~color)                 #color
